Note:
Java Lexer - Tokenizes Java source code into tokens for parsing

Supports complete Java language syntax including:
- All Java keywords (53 total): abstract, assert, boolean, break, byte, case, catch, char, class, const, continue, default, do, double, else, enum, extends, final, finally, float, for, goto, if, implements, import, instanceof, int, interface, long, native, new, package, private, protected, public, return, short, static, strictfp, super, switch, synchronized, this, throw, throws, transient, try, void, volatile, while
- Java operators: arithmetic, logical, bitwise, assignment, comparison
- Java literals: integers (decimal, hex, octal, binary), floating-point, character, string, boolean, null
- Annotations (@Override, @Deprecated, @SuppressWarnings, etc.)
- Comments: single-line (//), multi-line (/* */), JavaDoc (/** */)
- Separators: { } ( ) [ ] ; , . ...
- Generics: < > with proper nesting

Architecture:
- Token-based lexical analysis
- Line and column tracking for error reporting
- Proper handling of Java escape sequences
- Support for Unicode identifiers
- Complete operator tokenization including compound assignments
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

